# UI / shadcn conventions

## shadcn style
- Style preset: **base-nova**
- Underlying primitives: **`@base-ui/react`** (NOT Radix). Some Radix utilities
  (e.g. `@radix-ui/react-slot`) are installed where shadcn templates require.
- Auto-generated files live in `src/components/ui/`. Don't hand-edit unless
  adding a new variant; always run `npx shadcn add <component>` when possible.

## Theme tokens
- Primary: graphite dark (`oklch` of `#1a1a1a`-ish), accent gold (`#c9a961`).
- Color tokens are CSS variables defined in `src/app/globals.css`.
- Use semantic class names: `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`,
  `border-border`, etc. Avoid raw hex / `bg-[#xxx]`.

## Forms
Use shadcn `Form` wrapper with `react-hook-form` + `zod`:

```tsx
"use client"
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form"
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod"
import { z } from "zod"
import {
  Form, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormControl, FormMessage,
} from "@/components/ui/form"
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input"

const Schema = z.object({ email: z.string().email() })

export function MyForm() {
  const form = useForm<z.infer<typeof Schema>>({
    resolver: zodResolver(Schema),
    defaultValues: { email: "" },
  })
  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(/* ... */)} className="space-y-4">
        <FormField
          control={form.control}
          name="email"
          render={({ field }) => (
            <FormItem>
              <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>
              <FormControl><Input {...field} type="email" /></FormControl>
              <FormMessage />
            </FormItem>
          )}
        />
      </form>
    </Form>
  )
}
```

## Toast / feedback
- Mount `<Toaster />` from `@/components/ui/sonner` once in root layout.
- Use `toast.success(...)` / `toast.error(...)` from `sonner` after server
  action results.

## Loading & empty states
- Loading: render skeletons (`@/components/ui/skeleton`) at the same shape as
  the content. No bare spinners.
- Empty states: provide a brief message + primary CTA, never an empty page.

## Icons
- Always import from `lucide-react`.
- Default icon size matches button size variant; for inline text icons use
  `className="size-4"`.

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements need accessible labels.
- `<Input>` must be paired with `<Label>` (or `FormLabel`).
- Color contrast: don't rely on color alone for status — also use icons/badges.
